      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that math makes sense. but a lot of the people i talk to say there are hidden fees or stuff that makes it even harder to pay off. are there any other hidden costs i should be looking out for that might be eating my money?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the hidden fees and sneaky goblins lurking in the shadows of your loan agreement! While student loans are generally straightforward, there are a few potential hidden costs to be aware of:\n\n1. Late Payment Fees: If you miss a payment or pay it late, you might be hit with a fee. It's like a goblin demanding extra gold for being late to the feast.\n\n2. Origination Fees: Some loans have an origination fee, which is a charge for processing your loan. It's like paying a goblin for the privilege of borrowing their treasure.\n\n3. Prepayment Penalties: Some loans have penalties for paying off your loan early. It's like a goblin saying, \"You can't just take my gold without paying me a little extra.\"\n\n4. Interest Capitalization: If you have a deferment or forbearance, interest might not be capitalized (added to the principal) during that time. However, once you resume payments, the accumulated interest during the deferment or forbearance period could be capitalized, increasing your principal balance. It's like a goblin who decides to charge you for the interest you didn't pay while you were away.\n\n5. Administrative Fees: Some loans have fees for things like loan consolidation",
